President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in the State of Oregon due to a severe winter storm that occurred from February 11 to February 15, 2021. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Toney Raines has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.